Welcome

Welcome to the Experiment! In this experiment, we will give you two anagrams to solve. An anagram is simply a word or phrase formed by rearranging the letters of another word or phrase. For example:

  • POKER is an anagram of PKOER
  • PIKE is an anagram of KEPI

We kindly request for your full attention for the experiment and ask you to refrain from using Google or other search engines.

Please press the 'n' key to continue once you understand.

Instructions

When you click next, you will be presented with an anagram that will be displayed for 4 seconds. Following that, the same anagram will be presented to you again in a different configuration for 4 seconds.

In total, we will present the anagram to you in seven different configurations. If you have not figured the answer to the anagram by then, then at the eighth time, we will show a much easier configuration of that anagram to you.

As an example, you may be presented with random configurations such as: ONLEM, MOELN, NMEOL, and finally the easier configuration, LMEON. Here, these configurations come from the same anagram, LEMON and your goal was figuring out the underlying anagram.

Please press the 'm' key to continue once you understand.

Instructions

Now, we will present you the first anagram which you have to solve. We will present the anagram to you in seven different configurations. If you have not figured the answer to the anagram by then, then we will show a much easier configuration to you in the eighth iteration.

Please press the 'b' key to continue.

Now we will show you another configuration of the anagram

Now we will show you another configuration of the anagram

Now we will show you another configuration of the anagram

Now we will show you another configuration of the anagram

Now we will show you another configuration of the anagram
NICGARO
We will now show you a much easier configuration of this anagram

Instructions

Thank you for your attention so far. Now, you will be presented with the second anagram which you have to solve.

We will again present the anagram to you in seven different configurations. If you have not figured the answer to the anagram by then, then at the eighth time, we will show a much easier configuration of that anagram to you.

Please press the 'g' key to continue once you understand.
